# Bashcord Project Overview

Bashcord is a customized Discord client mod based on Equicord (which is a fork of Vencord). This project maintains its own branding and custom plugins while automatically syncing updates from the upstream Equicord repository.

## Key Project Structure

- **Main Entry Point**: [src/Vencord.ts](mdc:src/Vencord.ts) - Core initialization and welcome popup integration
- **Settings UI**: [src/plugins/_core/settings.tsx](mdc:src/plugins/_core/settings.tsx) - Customized settings with "Bashcord" branding
- **Custom Plugins**: [src/bashplugins/](mdc:src/bashplugins/) - Bashcord-specific plugins (moved from userplugins)
- **Welcome Modal**: [src/components/WelcomeModal.tsx](mdc:src/components/WelcomeModal.tsx) - Welcome popup for new users
- **Build Scripts**: [scripts/build/](mdc:scripts/build/) - Build system for plugins and main app
- **GitHub Workflows**: [.github/workflows/](mdc:.github/workflows/) - CI/CD for updates, building, and releases

## Important Branding Changes

- All "Equicord" references should be changed to "Bashcord" in user-facing text
- Settings tab labeled "Bashplugins" instead of "Plugins"
- Custom plugins directory is `bashplugins/` not `userplugins/`
- Release files should be prefixed with "bashcord" not "equibop"

## Protected Files During Updates

These files are protected during automatic Equicord updates:
- `src/plugins/_core/settings.tsx` - Bashcord branding
- `src/bashplugins/` - Custom Bashcord plugins
- `src/components/WelcomeModal.tsx` - Welcome popup
- `.github/workflows/` - Custom CI/CD workflows